    <screens>
        <name>Driving_Workforce_Agreement</name>
        <label>Driving Workforce Agreement</label>
        <locationX>772</locationX>
        <locationY>875</locationY>
        <allowBack>false</allowBack>
        <allowFinish>true</allowFinish>
        <allowPause>false</allowPause>
        <connector>
            <targetReference>Create_WTRT</targetReference>
        </connector>
        <fields>
            <name>BA_Text</name>
            <fieldText>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;font-size: 18px; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);&quot;&gt;Driving Workforce Agreement&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;Blue Arrow Limited has entered in to a Workforce Agreement with its mobile workers in relation to certain aspects of the Road Transport (Working Time Regulations) 2005, the Road Transport (Working Time) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2005, the Working Time Regulations 1998 and the Working Time Regulations (Northern Ireland) 1998.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;The Reference Period&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;Under the Workforce Agreement it has been agreed that the reference period over which working hours are calculated is extended from the current 17 weeks to 26 weeks. This will allow greater flexibility in terms of working hours as the weekly average hours worked by an individual will be calculated over a longer period. The change in the reference period will not impact on the relevant rest and break requirements imposed by statute (law) which still need to be adhered to.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;The Workforce Agreement also amends the start and end dates of the reference period to a fixed period of 1st October to 31st March and 1st April to 30th September of each year. This will amend the period which the reference period is assessed. These periods will need to be slightly adjusted to take in to account the variances in each calendar year but the reference period will not in any case extend beyond 26 weeks.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Night Work&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;The proposed Workforce Agreement has removed the 10 hour limit on night work allowing for greater flexibility, however the rest and break requirements imposed by statute (law) will remain and need to be adhered to.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</fieldText>
            <fieldType>DisplayText</fieldType>
            <visibilityRule>
                <conditionLogic>or</conditionLogic>
                <conditions>
                    <leftValueReference>Get_Candidate.Brand__c</leftValueReference>
                    <operator>IsNull</operator>
                    <rightValue>
                        <booleanValue>true</booleanValue>
                    </rightValue>
                </conditions>
                <conditions>
                    <leftValueReference>Get_Candidate.Brand__c</leftValueReference>
                    <operator>EqualTo</operator>
                    <rightValue>
                        <stringValue>Blue Arrow</stringValue>
                    </rightValue>
                </conditions>
            </visibilityRule>
        </fields>
        <fields>
            <name>Single_Multi</name>
            <choiceReferences>Option1</choiceReferences>
            <choiceReferences>Option2</choiceReferences>
            <dataType>String</dataType>
            <fieldText>Will you be driving for other agency&apos;s alongside Blue Arrow?</fieldText>
            <fieldType>RadioButtons</fieldType>
            <isRequired>true</isRequired>
        </fields>
        <fields>
            <name>Single_Engagment</name>
            <fieldText>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;I &lt;/span&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;{!Get_Candidate.FirstName}&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt; declare that:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;I have accurately detailed all my Working Time during the current reference period in the table below and warrant that it is true and correct to the best of my knowledge; and&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;I&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt; &lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;AM NOT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt; &lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;currently engaged in any work, other than for Blue Arrow, which needs to be included in the calculations of my Working Time under the WTRT Regulations; and&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;I will keep Blue Arrow informed in writing as to the details of Working Time undertaken for other employers or employment businesses on a weekly basis; and&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;I will inform Blue Arrow immediately if there are any changes to my situation which impacts on my Working Time.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</fieldText>
            <fieldType>DisplayText</fieldType>
            <visibilityRule>
                <conditionLogic>and</conditionLogic>
                <conditions>
                    <leftValueReference>Single_Multi</leftValueReference>
                    <operator>EqualTo</operator>
                    <rightValue>
                        <elementReference>Option1</elementReference>
                    </rightValue>
                </conditions>
            </visibilityRule>
        </fields>
        <fields>
            <name>Single_Confirm</name>
            <choiceReferences>AgreementVar</choiceReferences>
            <dataType>Boolean</dataType>
            <fieldText>Please confirm you agree with the above statement</fieldText>
            <fieldType>RadioButtons</fieldType>
            <isRequired>true</isRequired>
            <visibilityRule>
